  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 20.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And they brought him unto him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The father, it would seem, was not able of himself to bring him, so fierce and violent were the paroxysms of the disorder",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": ". And when he saw him, straightway the spirit tare him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "συνεσπέραξεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") - it might be rendered, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "convulsed",
        "children": []
